            , JUNIOR. My father is a woolen-draper. I paid the prisoner seven pounds two shillings, for an account that we had purchased the Friday before. This is the receipt he have me for it, (read) the receipt is his usual hand-writing.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18150405-125-person1102">
                  WILLIAM 
                  GEE
